tags.tag:
An in-memory xml-style data hierarchy. JavaScript: LzDataset Extends LzDataElement A dataset tag within a canvas or library element defines a local dataset. The name of the dataset is used in the datapath attribute of a view. The src attribute of the dataset element specifies whether the data is compiled into the application or fetched at runtime
When true, the server will accept encoded responses for this request. Encoded responses require more work for the LPS (encoding the response) and client (decoding the response) in trade for lower network bandwidth usage.
&value_boolean;
** Deprecated since 1.1 Use the request attribute instead. **
&value_boolean;
When true, the server will encode and send the HTTP response headers along with the data (defaults to false).
&value_boolean;
Sent when new data arrives for this dataset
Sent when an error occurs for this dataset
Sent when a request times out
** Deprecated since 1.1 Use the secureport attribute instead. ** Sets the port number to use to connect to the LPS for a secure connection.
A string to be appended to the request that the dataset makes.
If true, the client should ensure that each request is made, rather than just making and reporting the last request.
&value_boolean;
If true, the datset will make a request when it inits. The default for this is false.
&value_boolean;
specifies whether or not the app-LPS connection is secure
&value_boolean;
Sets the port number to use to connect to the LPS for a secure connection.
The source for requests made by this dataset.
If set to "http", then the dataset will interpret its src attribute as an url from which to load its content, rather than as a static xml file to inline.
&node;

A way of representing a server-side HTTP datasource. JavaScript: LzHTTPDatasource Extends Datasource The datasource tag is an optional way of representing a server side datasource. The datasource's parameters can specify ways in which the client is will make backend requests. Also, more than one dataset can share a datasource, and the datasource can be used to control session related information.
** Deprecated since 1.1 ** Use the dataset secureport attribute instead.
&node;

A simple date picker JavaScript: datepicker Extends Basedatepicker Datepicker is a simple component that makes it easy for users to select dates.
Set to true to initially show the datepicker as an icon, otherwise set to false.
&value_boolean;
&basedatepicker;

text input component with lz components look and feel JavaScript: edittext Extends Baseformitem The edittext tag provides a text input field which has a look and feel to match the lz component set. It can accept any inputtext attribute.
Set to true for multiple lines, default: false.
&value_boolean;
Set to true for a password field. Text will appear as ****, default: false.
&value_boolean;
Set to true if you plan to change the width or height of the component at run-time, default: false.
&value_boolean;
&basevaluecomponent;

Presents a grid backed by a datasource. JavaScript: grid Extends Basegrid A grid is be used to present data in a dataset. Although it can be configured using gridcolumn and gridtext, by default it will present an editable field either for each attribute in the first data node in the grid.
If false, the grid will never show a horizontal scrollbar, even if the rows are wider than the grid.
&basegrid;

An abstract column in a grid. JavaScript: basegridcolumn Extends Basecomponent basegridcolumn can be used in basegrids or grids to customize the look of both the column header and the row contents for that column. In cases where a standard column header look is desired, but the contents may vary, use gridcolumn.
If set to false, the field will not be editable.
&gridcolumn;

Provides a horizontal scrollbar. JavaScript: hscrollbar Extends Basescrollbar A scrollbar manipulates the x or y position of a target view that is clipped by its parent, creating a scrolling effect when the user clicks up/down arrows, clicks on the scroll track or drags the thumb.
If this is defined, it will be used as the scrollbar's background color when it is disabled. If not provided, the scrollbar will use the bgcolor of its closest parent that has a bgcolor defined.
&basescrollbar;

The basic input-text element. JavaScript: LzInputText Extends LzAbstractText This tag creates an area of the canvas that the user can use to edit text. It is equivalent to the HTML input type="text", input type="password", and textarea tags.
If true, the text field will automatically wrap long lines of text at the right margin, and allow the user to press enter on their keyboard to add a line break to the text. The default for this attribute is false.
&value_boolean;
If true, the input text field acts like a password input field; any text typed in appears as "****" characters in the current font.
&value_boolean;
If true, this text field can be dynamically resized at runtime.
&value_boolean;
If true, the width of the text field will be recomputed each time setText() is called, so that the text view is exactly as wide as the width of the widest line.
&value_boolean;
If true, the text is selectable
&value_boolean;
The text to display in this text field.
&view;

A pull-down menu that can be used within a menubar, a menuitem or any other view. JavaScript: menu Extends Basecomponent The menu tag creates a menu that floats above all other views when activated. If a menu is a subview of a menubar, then it will create a "menubutton" in the menubar with the its text attribute equal to that of the menu's. This "menubutton" inherits its properties from button.
a string to indicate how the floating part of the menu attaches to the menubutton or menuitem. Possible values are: 'top', 'bottom', 'left', and 'right'
a boolean indicating whether or not the menu is in opened
&value_boolean;
&basecomponent;

An item in a pull-down menu. JavaScript: menuitem Extends Textlistitem The menuitem tag provides a menu item within the menu tag. To associate a set of key commands with a menuitem, create a LzCommand object with an execution script (onselect="expression"), and then set the command attribute of the menuitem equal to the reference of that LzCommand object.
the command object assigned to be executed when this menuitem is selected
&textlistitem;

A horizontal separator for pull-down menus. JavaScript: menuseparator Extends Basecomponent The menuseparator tag provides a horizontal separator for pull-down menus. This tag must reside within a menu tag.
the number of pixels to inset the menuseparartor from the sides of the menu
&basecomponent;

Param tag for remotecall. JavaScript: param Extends Node Tag to declaratively set parameter values for remotecall. If a getValue method is declared in the body of remotecall, use its return as value for paramter. If both getValue method and value attribute are set in param, getValue wins.
Value to use for paramter. A getValue() method can be declared inside param to use its return as the parameter value. If both value attribute and getValue method are declared, param will use getValue().
&node;
